    return ( this.name + &quot; &quot; + this.age );

… implicitly generates a string from your `int` member field, `this.age`.

That is equivalent to a call to [`String.valueof`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/String.html#valueOf(int)):

    return ( this.name + &quot; &quot; + String.valueOf( this.age ) );

See [*Converting Numbers to Strings*](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/data/converting.html) in the *Java Tutorials* provided by Oracle free of cost.

